msgctxt "sn21.2:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 21 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 21 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn21.2:0.2"
msgid "1. Bhikkhuvagga "
msgstr "1. Monks "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 2. Upatissasutta → sāriputtasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "sn21.2:0.3"
msgid "2. Upatissasutta "
msgstr "2. With Upatissa "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn21.2:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn21.2:1.2"
msgid "Tatra kho āyasmā sāriputto bhikkhū āmantesi: "
msgstr "There Sāriputta addressed the mendicants: "

msgctxt "sn21.2:1.3"
msgid "“āvuso bhikkhave”ti. "
msgstr "“Reverends, mendicants!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn21.2:1.4"
msgid "“Āvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato sāriputtassa paccassosuṃ. "
msgstr "“Reverend,” they replied. "

msgctxt "sn21.2:1.5"
msgid "Āyasmā sāriputto etadavoca: "
msgstr "Sāriputta said this: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn21.2:2.1"
msgid "“Idha mayhaṃ, āvuso, rahogatassa paṭisallīnassa evaṃ cetaso parivitakko udapādi: "
msgstr "“Just now, reverends, as I was in private retreat this thought came to mind: "

msgctxt "sn21.2:2.2"
msgid "‘atthi nu kho taṃ kiñci lokasmiṃ yassa me vipariṇāmaññathābhāvā uppajjeyyuṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā’ti? "
msgstr "‘Is there anything in the world whose changing and perishing would give rise to sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress in me?’ "

msgctxt "sn21.2:2.3"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, āvuso, etadahosi: "
msgstr "It occurred to me: "

msgctxt "sn21.2:2.4"
msgid "‘natthi kho taṃ kiñci lokasmiṃ yassa me vipariṇāmaññathābhāvā uppajjeyyuṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā’”ti. "
msgstr "‘There is nothing in the world whose changing and perishing would give rise to sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress in me.’” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.275, sc3
msgctxt "sn21.2:3.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā ānando āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When he said this, Venerable Ānanda said to him, "

msgctxt "sn21.2:3.2"
msgid "“satthupi kho te, āvuso sāriputta, vipariṇāmaññathābhāvā nuppajjeyyuṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā”ti? "
msgstr "“Even if the Teacher were to decay and perish? Wouldn’t that give rise to sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress in you?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn21.2:3.3"
msgid "“Satthupi kho me, āvuso, vipariṇāmaññathābhāvā nuppajjeyyuṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā, api ca me evamassa: "
msgstr "“Even if the Teacher were to decay and perish, that wouldn’t give rise to sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress in me. Still, I would think: "

msgctxt "sn21.2:3.4"
msgid "‘mahesakkho vata bho satthā antarahito mahiddhiko mahānubhāvo. "
msgstr "‘Alas, the illustrious Teacher, so mighty and powerful, has vanished! "

# NOTE: text omits close quotes.
msgctxt "sn21.2:3.5"
msgid "Sace hi bhagavā ciraṃ dīghamaddhānaṃ tiṭṭheyya tadassa bahujanahitāya bahujanasukhāya lokānukampāya atthāya hitāya sukhāya devamanussānan’ti. "
msgstr "If the Buddha was to remain for a long time, that would be for the welfare and happiness of the people, for the benefit, welfare, and happiness of gods and humans.’” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn21.2:3.6"
msgid "Tathā hi panāyasmato sāriputtassa dīgharattaṃ ahaṅkāramamaṅkāramānānusayā susamūhatā. "
msgstr "“That must be because Venerable Sāriputta has long ago totally eradicated ego, possessiveness, and the underlying tendency to conceit. "

msgctxt "sn21.2:3.7"
msgid "Tasmā āyasmato sāriputtassa satthupi vipariṇāmaññathābhāvā nuppajjeyyuṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā”ti. "
msgstr "So even if the Teacher were to decay and perish, it wouldn’t give rise to sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and distress in him.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn21.2:3.8"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

